  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes from her mother's memoir, ''Trying to Get to Heaven: Opinions of a Tennessee Talker'', by Dixie Carter (Simon and Schuster, 1996):\\n\\n\"My children were born one year, one month, and nineteen days apart, Ginna (Rosalind Helen Virginia, for Arthur's mother, Aunt Helen, and Gina) on May 17, 1969, and Mary Dixie (for Aunt Mary and me) on July 6, 1970. [...] at Leroy Hospital on East Sixty-first Street [...] At 11:21 that morning my baby [Ginna] was born - a girl , a rosebud miniature of her father, which fact made me instantly fonder of him than ever.\"\\n\\n(Wikipedia has wrong year of birth, and wrong order of birth of her and her sister). \\n",
